# Citation File Format — https://citation-file-format.github.io/
# Run `cffconvert -i CITATION.cff -f bibtex` to get a BibTeX entry.
cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Riprap: composable citation-grounded climate briefings for any US place"
type: software
message: >-
  If you use Riprap, or its multi-city framework / BYOD pebble system,
  in research or applied civic work, please cite it.
authors:
  - given-names: Adam
    family-names: Rahman
    name-particle: Munawar
    email: msrahmanadam@gmail.com
    affiliation: "Independent"
repository-code: "https://github.com/msradam/riprap"
abstract: >-
  Riprap composes ~25 federal, state, and city public-record data
  sources into a citation-grounded climate-exposure briefing for any
  US address. NYC is the reference deployment; Chicago, Seattle, San
  Francisco, Boston, and Albany run on the same code via per-city YAML
  pebble manifests. Every numeric claim in a briefing links back to a
  primary public-record source; the reconciler (IBM Granite 4.1 with
  Mellea rejection sampling) refuses to ship a sentence it cannot
  ground. Compliance audit covers 13 predicates derived from FEMA,
  IPCC AR6, TCFD, ASTM E1527-21, EPA/CDC CERC, AP Stylebook, SPJ.
keywords:
  - civic-tech
  - flood-risk
  - climate-exposure
  - citation-grounded
  - rag
  - grounded-llm
  - open-data
  - socrata
  - ckan
  - fema-nfhl
  - noaa-coops
  - npcc4
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.6.0
date-released: "2026-07-11"

# How Riprap depends on prior work. We cite the data sources Riprap
# composes in each per-pebble manifest's `provenance` block (see
# deployments/<city>/manifests/*.yaml); the items below are the
# foundation-model and methodology references.
references:
  - type: article
    title: "Granite 4.1 Language Models"
    authors:
      - family-names: "IBM Research"
    year: 2025
    notes: "Reconciler LLM. Apache-2.0. https://huggingface.co/ibm-granite"
  - type: article
    title: "Prithvi-EO 2.0: A versatile multi-temporal foundation model for Earth observation"
    authors:
      - family-names: "Jakubik"
        given-names: "Johannes"
    year: 2024
    notes: "Satellite-attributable flood segmentation. Apache-2.0."
  - type: software
    title: "TerraMind: a foundation model for Earth observation"
    authors:
      - family-names: "ESA"
    notes: "LULC + buildings. Apache-2.0."
  - type: article
    title: "New York City Panel on Climate Change 2024 Report (NPCC4)"
    authors:
      - family-names: "Rosenzweig"
        given-names: "Cynthia"
    year: 2024
    journal: "Annals of the New York Academy of Sciences"
    volume: 1539
    doi: "10.1111/nyas.15116"
